  hook:"A flat, dark panel sits on a rooftop. It has no moving parts, burns no fuel, produces no emissions, makes no noise. Yet it converts sunlight — photons traveling 150 million kilometers from the Sun at the speed of light — directly into electricity. No turbines, no steam, no combustion. Just photons hitting silicon and electrons flowing. Solar panels are the most elegant energy technology ever invented — and they're now the cheapest source of new electricity in most of the world. India added over 15 GW of solar capacity in 2023 alone and aims for 500 GW by 2030. How does a piece of glass and silicon turn sunlight into the electricity powering your life?",
